CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 28, 1951, pg. 11, reads: "Jabberwocky Jabberwock...was truly gay this year with A. Leo Weil School housing the amusing annual event presented by Delta Sigma Theta sorors. ...Right: Miss Nancy Lee, president of Alpha Epsilon Chapter, and general chairman, Thelma Watson. - Harris Photos."  Article reads: "AKAs Capture First Prize in Jabberwock - Curiousity [Curiosity]? Yes, that was the theme of the Delta Sigma Theta's first Jabberwock in five years and it was a tremendous comeback.  The affair was held Friday, April 20 and was a night of fun and laughter for Pittsburghers...."
TitMainTitle: Nancy Lee and Thelma Watson shaking hands, at A. Leo Weil School, for Delta Sigma Theta's Jabberwock
